      • DATA_SET_ID

        public static final java.lang.String DATA_SET_ID
        Current data set id. The data set id is used to distinguish between different data synchronisation sets: the application may be running using a set A, but if the user triggers data syncronization or if the periodic task requests data synchronization, we then have to store the new data set in the database without interfering with the currently used data set, and this id is used for that purpose. Once the data sync operation is successfully terminated, the application will use the new data set and the old one will be deleted.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
